## 7. Lifecycle Cohorts & Leading Indicators (Andrew Chen)

### Cohort Analysis Framework

For every monthly signup cohort, track:
- **D1, D7, D30 retention** (% still active)
- **Activation rate** (% who placed first automated trade)
- **Revenue retention** ($ at D30, D60, D90)
- **Engagement depth** (dashboard visits per week)

**Leading indicators that predict churn:**
- Never activated automation (stayed in Intelligence tier, never upgraded)
- Didn't open dashboard for 7+ consecutive days
- Kill switch enabled for >14 days straight
- Zero journal entries in first 30 days (disengagement signal)

**Action:** Build cohort dashboard in admin view. Alert when a cohort shows weak activation (<20% in first 7 days).

