## 10. The Law of Shitty Clickthroughs (Andrew Chen)

> "Over time, all marketing channels decay as users become saturated."

**What this means for Winzinvest:**

Your first channel (likely r/algotrading, Twitter fintwit, maybe Product Hunt) will work great initially, then decay. Plan for **channel sequencing**:

**Early stage (now — first 500 customers):**
1. Direct communities (r/algotrading, r/options, fintwit)
2. Word of mouth from Founding Members
3. Performance sharing (social proof loop)

**Growth stage (500 — 5,000 customers):**
1. SEO content (trading discipline, automation guides)
2. YouTube (system walkthrough, performance reviews)
3. Partnerships (brokerage integrations, influencer collabs)

**Scale stage (5,000+):**
1. Paid acquisition (if CAC supports it)
2. Lifecycle marketing (reactivation, upsells)
3. Enterprise (wealth managers, family offices)

**Key:** Start building channel 2 before channel 1 saturates.

