## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### ❌ Scaling before PMF (Sean Ellis)
Don't run paid ads, hire salespeople, or build tons of features until you hit 40%+ on the Ellis test. The Founding Member phase is for **finding PMF**, not scaling.

### ❌ Pitch-slapping every user (Elena Verna)
Don't spam every waitlist signup with sales emails. Qualify based on behavior (dashboard visits, questions asked) before reaching out personally.

### ❌ Ignoring retention for acquisition (Andrew Chen)
If D7 retention is <40%, fix the product experience before spending money on ads. Bad retention means bad PMF.

### ❌ Generic viral loops (Andrew Chen)
"Share Winzinvest and get $20 off" is a generic recipe. Won't work. The loop must be **performance-driven**: "My account is up 12% this quarter, here's how."

